# stockJEDI - Project Explanation

## What is stockJEDI?

stockJEDI is an **AI-powered stock intelligence and investment analysis platform**. It takes a stock ticker symbol (or a URL from a financial website) and produces a full institutional-style investment report — complete with machine learning predictions, technical indicators, sentiment analysis, and an AI-written narrative report.

---

## High-Level Architecture

The project is a **full-stack application** with three main components:

1. **Frontend** — A Next.js (React) web dashboard where users interact with the system.
2. **Backend** — A FastAPI (Python) REST API that orchestrates all analysis.
3. **ML Pipeline** — A standalone machine learning training pipeline that produces prediction models used by the backend.

These components communicate over HTTP/REST APIs, with Redis for caching and PostgreSQL for persistent storage.

```
User Browser
    |
    v
[Frontend: Next.js :3000]
    |  (HTTP REST)
    v
[Backend: FastAPI :8000]
    |
    +-----> [Yahoo Finance API]       (market data)
    +-----> [News/Social APIs]         (sentiment data)
    +-----> [Groq API: LLaMA 3.3 70B] (AI report generation)
    +-----> [Redis]                    (caching)
    +-----> [PostgreSQL]               (user data, watchlists, portfolios)
    +-----> [ML Models on disk]        (XGBoost, LSTM, Prophet, Ensemble)
```

