## Infrastructure and Deployment

### Docker Compose (5 Services)
The project is fully containerized with `docker-compose.yml`:

| Service | Image | Port | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| **db** | postgres:15-alpine | 5432 | PostgreSQL database |
| **redis** | redis:7-alpine | 6379 | Caching layer |
| **migrate** | custom backend image | - | Runs Alembic DB migrations at startup |
| **backend** | custom Python image | 8000 | FastAPI API server |
| **frontend** | custom Node.js image | 3000 | Next.js web app |

A `docker-compose.dev.yml` provides development overrides with hot-reload volumes.

### Nginx Reverse Proxy (`deployment/nginx.conf`)
- TLS/SSL termination (TLS 1.2 and 1.3)
- Rate limiting (10 req/s general, 5 req/s for auth endpoints)
- Security headers: HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options
- Proxies `/api/*` to the backend and everything else to the frontend

### Kubernetes (`deployment/kubernetes.yaml`)
- 3-replica backend Deployment
- ClusterIP Service for internal communication

### CI/CD (`.github/workflows/main.yml`)
- GitHub Actions pipeline for testing, building Docker images, and deployment

